to play Bh6.} h6 10. c4 {Getting rid of the centralized Knight.} Nc7 11. Nc3 {
Developing the Knight on it's natural square.} Ne6 12. Re1 {Overprotecting e5.}
d6 13. b3 {Solidifying the Queen-side and preparing to play Bb2.} Bb7 14. Bb2 {
Developing the Bishop and preparing Rad1.} O-O 15. Rad1 {White is ready to
increate the pressure over the d6 pawn with Ne4 next.} *

