the Queen if he wants it back.} Qa5+ 7. Nbd2 {The best way to block the check,
supporting the pawn push to c4 in some lines, and making room for Rb1-Pb4.}
Qxc5 {Black's best option, but not the most played move!} 8. O-O {Rushing to
castle, and play for a quick e5.} d6 {Preparing to develop the Knight.} 9. Re1
{Preparing to play e5.} Nf6 10. Nb3 {Attacking the Queen, and preparing to
break with e5.} Qb6 {Is a safer option for Black and i covered it in great
depth in the main course.} *

