Knight.} Nxd2 13. Bxd2 {Preparing Bc3 to solidify the center.} Na5 {
Threatening to play Bb5, swapping the bad Bishop.} 14. Bd3 {Preparing to hide
the Bishop on c2 when Black tries to trade it.} Bb5 15. Bc2 {Keeping the
strong Bishop.} Rc8 16. Rc1 {Bringing the Rook in the game, preparing Bb1.} Qb6
17. Bc3 {Overprotecting d4.} Nc4 18. Bb1 {Improving the Bishop.} O-O 19. h4 {
White has attacking chances on the King-side. ½-½
