from being that simple for Black.Now let me highlight the positive aspects of
8. dxc5!So what is exactly this move, and why are we doing it?So the big point
is that we are avoiding cxd4 with Nb4, and this way we get to keep the strong
Bishop on d3.On the other hand, the b1 Knight was lacking a good square, and
