[White "Short and Sweet"]
[Black "2...Nf6"]
[Result "*"]
[PlyCount "25"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nf6 {The romantic Nimzowitsch Variation!This is the pet line
of GM Rakhmanov.Although he has a lot of games with it, most of the players
are using it as a surprise weapon, so you just have to be prepared with the
common knowledge that i am about to teach you, because you never really know
when you are about to face this line.} 3. e5 {The most principled reaction,
taking space with tempo.} Nd5 4. Nc3 {I like this move because it's inviting a
strategical game. 4.d4 has been also played a lot, trying to directly refute
Black's set-up.First of all, i don't think that is the refutation, and second,
it is not a very practical approach because as i said, this is a surprise
weapon, and it's not smart to do a memory contest with someone that looked it
up that morning.} Nxc3 {Rakhmanov's Pet Line, entering a complex pawn
structure.The danger of working on this line is that any random engine would
show you +0.5 with any move, but we have to go a little bit deeper with it.
First of all you can ask yourself, why is a 2680 GM
@@StartBracket@@Rakhmanov@@EndBracket@@ playing this line for more than 20
times knowing that the engine gives white +0.5, and his opponents can prepare
against it? Is he deliberately trying to get an inferior position or is it
that he thinks the positions are definitely not as easy as they seem?} 5. dxc3
{White is preparing to develop with Bf4-Qd2-0-0-0. This set-up will put
annoying pressure on the backward d7 pawn.} Nc6 6. Bf4 Qb6 {Rakhmanov's
favorite move!} 7. b3 {The most flexible keeping options to castle on both
sides!} Qc7 8. Qd2 e6 9. h4 {Taking space on the King-side is always a good
idea, whether if Black castles long or short.} h6 10. h5 {Notice that White is
improving the position while waiting to see what Black is up to.} b6 11. Bd3 {
Staying flexible is the best!Not showing our plan yet!} Bb7 12. Be4 Be7 {If
Black still tries to keep options, we can simply rook lift:} 13. Rh3 {It's not
gonna be easy for Black to answer Rg3.} *

